ice feeds from Chainlink and other providers, ensuring minimal basis risk. The funding rate reflects the premium/discount between the perpetual price and the oracle-derived index price. Long positions pay short positions when rates are positive, with payments processed automatically through smart contracts. GMX's oracle dependency means funding rates respond directly to external market conditions rather than internal order book imbalances."}]]}],"$Lf",["$L10","$L11","$L12"],"$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]]}]
